Like most college football players, Julian Okwara always fantasized about the day he would be drafted by an NFL team.
“You imagine yourself walking onto the stage, wearing your suit and a nice watch,” the defensive end out of Notre Dame told The Post.
“I was going to get dapper.”Influenced by Conor McGregor’s rakish style, the 22-year-old enlisted the fighter’s tailor David August to make his ensemble for this year’s draft.
This year, the league even planned to have prospects arrive to the stage, crossing the Bellagio fountains in boats.
“CJ loves Dior,” said Creatiz, who had tapped the fashion house to design his draft suit.